WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.627 --> 00:00:04.629
♪ ♪

2
00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:24.107
{\an8}Ready for the big
history test today. Susmita?

3
00:00:24.107 --> 00:00:26.192
{\an8}Does this look ready? Mmm.

4
00:00:26.192 --> 00:00:27.318
{\an8}- Oh. wow.
- Uh. yeah.

5
00:00:27.318 --> 00:00:28.528
{\an8}I stayed up
pretty late studying.

6
00:00:28.528 --> 00:00:30.739
{\an8}I'm not as confident as you.
but. uh. history.

7
00:00:30.739 --> 00:00:34.034
{\an8}how hard can it be?
It happened already. (laughs)

8
00:00:34.034 --> 00:00:35.201
{\an8}Oh. hey. Chelsea.

9
00:00:35.201 --> 00:00:37.120
{\an8}Um. you're making
a lot of eye contact.

10
00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:38.538
{\an8}Are you ready for the test?

11
00:00:38.538 --> 00:00:39.581
{\an8}Mm-hmm. Yeah.

12
00:00:39.581 --> 00:00:41.708
{\an8}Well. if you studied hard.

13
00:00:41.708 --> 00:00:43.460
{\an8}I'm sure you'll...

14
00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:44.878
{\an8}- do great.
- (moans mockingly)

15
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:46.046
{\an8}Okay. cool.

16
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:48.214
{\an8}Just gonna
talk to Susmita again.

17
00:00:48.214 --> 00:00:50.050
{\an8}Hey. Susmita.
You ready for the test?

18
00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:51.885
{\an8}I already asked you that.
Sorry. sorry.

19
00:00:51.885 --> 00:00:52.927
{\an8} <i>If you need a lot of fish ♪</i>

20
00:00:52.927 --> 00:00:54.387
{\an8} <i>In a jiffy ♪</i>

21
00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:56.723
{\an8}<i>♪ Call Jeffrey Ruth
Seafood Delivery ♪</i>

22
00:00:56.723 --> 00:00:57.807
{\an8}- MS. TWITCHELL: Gene.
- Yes?

23
00:00:57.807 --> 00:00:58.808
{\an8}Please stop singing that.

24
00:00:58.808 --> 00:01:00.060
{\an8}What. we're not allowed to sing

25
00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:02.020
{\an8}radio jingles
during quiet reading time?

26
00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:03.480
{\an8}- You're not.
- Can I hum it?

27
00:01:03.480 --> 00:01:05.023
{\an8}- Nope.
<i>- FROND: Hello. Wagstaffians.</i>

28
00:01:05.023 --> 00:01:06.733
{\an8}<i>If I could have
your attention. please.</i>

29
00:01:06.733 --> 00:01:09.444
{\an8}LOUISE: Ms. Labonz. wait.
Mr. Frond needs our attention.

30
00:01:09.444 --> 00:01:11.029
{\an8}- (Labonz grunts)
<i>- I'd like to remind everyone</i>

31
00:01:11.029 --> 00:01:13.823
{\an8}<i>about my new thera-doll
"Accountability Billy."</i>

32
00:01:13.823 --> 00:01:15.867
{\an8}<i>When you see your fellow
classmates doing anything wrong.</i>

33
00:01:15.867 --> 00:01:18.453
{\an8}<i>write it down. and put it
in Billy's little fanny pack.</i>

34
00:01:18.453 --> 00:01:21.122
{\an8}<i>And then I help Billy go through
the notes every morning.</i>

35
00:01:21.122 --> 00:01:24.084
{\an8}Don't worry. it is cool
to tattle on your friends.

36
00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:26.920
{\an8}You know the saying:
"Everyone loves a tattle tale."

37
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:29.923
{\an8}So. Neil Roberts. Billy wants
to see you in my office.

38
00:01:29.923 --> 00:01:31.257
{\an8}Unrelated. thank you. Rudy.

39
00:01:31.257 --> 00:01:33.802
{\an8}What? No. No. Not me.

40
00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:36.721
{\an8}<i>TINA:
Okay. getting to the end here.</i>

41
00:01:36.721 --> 00:01:38.223
{\an8}<i>Boom. Easy peasy. Heh.</i>

42
00:01:38.223 --> 00:01:39.808
{\an8}<i>Another one. Boom again.</i>

43
00:01:39.808 --> 00:01:41.935
{\an8}<i>Dang. you're good. Tina.
Last question.</i>

44
00:01:41.935 --> 00:01:42.977
{\an8}<i>Yup. I know this one.</i>

45
00:01:42.977 --> 00:01:45.105
{\an8}<i>I. um. think.</i>

46
00:01:45.105 --> 00:01:47.482
{\an8}<i>Wait. No.
That doesn't feel right.</i>

47
00:01:48.525 --> 00:01:50.276
{\an8}<i>Okay. phew.
There it is. Final answer.</i>

48
00:01:50.276 --> 00:01:52.570
{\an8}<i>Well. look at that.
Susmita also picked "C."</i>

49
00:01:52.570 --> 00:01:53.947
{\an8}<i>Wait. whoops.</i>

50
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:55.573
{\an8}<i>Don't-don't look at her test.
That's not good.</i>

51
00:01:55.573 --> 00:01:57.617
{\an8}<i>Um. let's make sure
nobody saw me doing that.</i>

52
00:01:57.617 --> 00:01:59.911
{\an8}<i>-Ah!</i>
- You're cheating.

53
00:01:59.911 --> 00:02:01.162
{\an8}- No. I'm not.
- What?

54
00:02:01.162 --> 00:02:03.456
{\an8}Nothing. (gasps)
You're cheating.

55
00:02:03.456 --> 00:02:04.624
You're cheating right now.

56
00:02:04.624 --> 00:02:06.126
You're writing down
all of her answers.

57
00:02:06.126 --> 00:02:07.627
No. I am not.

58
00:02:07.627 --> 00:02:08.712
- Yes. you are.
- What?

59
00:02:08.712 --> 00:02:09.921
- Nothing. nothing. Sorry. Sorry.
- Shh.

60
00:02:09.921 --> 00:02:11.339
- (Tina groans)
- (bell rings)

61
00:02:11.339 --> 00:02:13.383
All right. bring your
tests to the front.

62
00:02:13.383 --> 00:02:16.386
and go be in
someone else's classroom.

63
00:02:16.386 --> 00:02:17.846
Wait. Chelsea. can we talk?

64
00:02:17.846 --> 00:02:19.139
Um...

65
00:02:19.139 --> 00:02:20.473
Uh. hang on. Chelsea. Heh.

66
00:02:20.473 --> 00:02:23.560
Chelsea? Chelsea!

67
00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:25.228
<i>If you need a lot of fish ♪</i>

68
00:02:25.228 --> 00:02:26.730
<i>In a jiffy ♪</i>

69
00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:29.107
<i>♪ Call Jeffrey Ruth
Seafood Delivery ♪</i>

70
00:02:29.107 --> 00:02:30.608
So. is that
a thing you do now?

71
00:02:30.608 --> 00:02:32.027
Sing that jingle?

72
00:02:32.027 --> 00:02:33.611
I don't even notice
I'm doing it anymore.

73
00:02:33.611 --> 00:02:35.280
- We do.
- I heard it on the radio.

74
00:02:35.280 --> 00:02:37.907
like. one time.
I guess it's stuck in my head.

75
00:02:37.907 --> 00:02:39.534
Well. I don't get songs
stuck in my head.

76
00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:41.911
'cause my head isn't like
a big gooshy ball of bubble gum

77
00:02:41.911 --> 00:02:42.996
that things can get stuck in.

78
00:02:42.996 --> 00:02:44.497
It's already in my head.

79
00:02:44.497 --> 00:02:46.958
<i>♪ Call bum-bum. bloop-blop
bip bi-bippy ♪</i>

80
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:48.126
Now there's that version.

81
00:02:48.126 --> 00:02:49.127
<i>Na-dippy ♪</i>

82
00:02:49.127 --> 00:02:50.420
Hey. so this just might be

83
00:02:50.420 --> 00:02:51.838
my tiny. child body talking.

84
00:02:51.838 --> 00:02:53.715
but is our house freezing?

85
00:02:53.715 --> 00:02:55.258
I turned up the heat
a little before dinner.

86
00:02:55.258 --> 00:02:56.551
It should warm up in here soon.

87
00:02:56.551 --> 00:02:57.802
In the meantime. I feel like

88
00:02:57.802 --> 00:02:58.845
I should go put on a bra.

89
00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:00.221
Or at least some pasties.

90
00:03:00.221 --> 00:03:02.015
{\an8}Look at these little diamonds.

91
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.767
Wait. Tina. you had
your big history test today.

92
00:03:03.767 --> 00:03:05.143
- How was it?
- It was great.

93
00:03:05.143 --> 00:03:07.062
I definitely didn't cheat.
(nervous laughter)

94
00:03:07.062 --> 00:03:08.730
Anyway. can you
pass the spaghetti?

95
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:10.148
Sure. Wait. what?

96
00:03:10.148 --> 00:03:11.941
- Nothing.
- Okay.

97
00:03:11.941 --> 00:03:14.069
Thanks. Mmm. so good.

98
00:03:14.069 --> 00:03:15.862
Uh-oh. that's too big a bite.

99
00:03:15.862 --> 00:03:16.863
A gigabyte?

100
00:03:16.863 --> 00:03:18.990
Gonna push it back in my mouth.

101
00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:20.575
- Good work.
- <i>Boo-ba-dippy ♪</i>

102
00:03:20.575 --> 00:03:24.621
(Tina groaning)

103
00:03:24.621 --> 00:03:26.748
LOUISE:
Tina? It's your
brother and sister.

104
00:03:26.748 --> 00:03:28.500
- GENE: From childhood?
- We couldn't help but notice

105
00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:31.628
you were acting more not normal
than usual at dinner tonight.

106
00:03:31.628 --> 00:03:33.129
And there was nothing on TV.

107
00:03:33.129 --> 00:03:34.714
so we decided
to come check on you.

108
00:03:34.714 --> 00:03:36.675
- Thanks. but I'm good.
- She seems great.

109
00:03:36.675 --> 00:03:38.301
Okay fine. Shut the door.

110
00:03:38.301 --> 00:03:41.054
Something kind of happened
during the history test today.

111
00:03:41.054 --> 00:03:42.305
Not an interesting start.

112
00:03:42.305 --> 00:03:43.473
I was taking the test

113
00:03:43.473 --> 00:03:46.017
and I kind of glanced
at Susmita's test.

114
00:03:46.017 --> 00:03:48.520
But I didn't mean to look.
and I looked away fast.

115
00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:49.813
But this other girl. Chelsea.

116
00:03:49.813 --> 00:03:51.189
was also looking
at Susmita's test.

117
00:03:51.189 --> 00:03:53.066
and she was just copying down
all of her answers.

118
00:03:53.066 --> 00:03:55.235
- Getting interesting-er.
- But Chelsea saw me

119
00:03:55.235 --> 00:03:56.861
look at Susmita's test
and she called me a cheater.

120
00:03:56.861 --> 00:03:58.071
And when I tried to
find her after class

121
00:03:58.071 --> 00:03:59.406
to talk to her. she was gone.

122
00:03:59.406 --> 00:04:01.533
So what? Now you're worried
she's gonna tell on you?

123
00:04:01.533 --> 00:04:02.867
What? I didn't even
think about that.

124
00:04:02.867 --> 00:04:04.577
I feel like
we're already helping.

125
00:04:04.577 --> 00:04:06.454
Well. do you think
she's gonna tell on you?

126
00:04:06.454 --> 00:04:08.373
I mean. she doesn't seem like
the telling on people type.

127
00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:11.001
since she's. you know.
basically. uh. a criminal.

128
00:04:11.001 --> 00:04:12.043
She's the girl
who got in trouble

129
00:04:12.043 --> 00:04:13.837
for saying the F-word 23 times

130
00:04:13.837 --> 00:04:15.422
during one game of kickball
and she got suspended.

131
00:04:15.422 --> 00:04:16.631
Is that the same girl

132
00:04:16.631 --> 00:04:18.216
who spray-painted
the F-word on the bleachers?

133
00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:20.051
Yeah. she really
likes the F-word.

134
00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:22.554
So. do you think
she thinks you'll tell on her?

135
00:04:22.554 --> 00:04:24.347
Uh. I mean. I'm not sure.

136
00:04:24.347 --> 00:04:25.557
Well. let me help you out.

137
00:04:25.557 --> 00:04:27.434
Of course she thinks
you're gonna tell on her.

138
00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:28.727
You're a hall monitor.

139
00:04:28.727 --> 00:04:30.353
A really cool hall monitor?

140
00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:31.938
I've been calling people
"Tiger" a lot lately.

141
00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:33.523
Like. "Slow down there. Tiger."
Heh.

142
00:04:33.523 --> 00:04:35.191
- Pretty cool.
- I'm just saying.

143
00:04:35.191 --> 00:04:37.068
if you saw this girl cheating.
and she saw you cheating...

144
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:38.695
- I wasn't.
- ...she might think

145
00:04:38.695 --> 00:04:41.239
she has to tell on you
before you tell on her.

146
00:04:41.239 --> 00:04:43.158
I'm not gonna tell on her.
I'm terrified of her.

147
00:04:43.158 --> 00:04:45.201
And maybe she knows that.
but maybe she thinks

148
00:04:45.201 --> 00:04:46.745
you might
tell on her anonymously.

149
00:04:46.745 --> 00:04:48.329
like say.
by writing it on a note

150
00:04:48.329 --> 00:04:50.832
and stuffing it in a certain
little doll's fanny pack?

151
00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:52.751
Oh. my God.
Accountability Billy.

152
00:04:52.751 --> 00:04:54.127
W-What do I do?
I'm freaking out. (panting)

153
00:04:54.127 --> 00:04:55.754
Do you need more spaghetti?
Never mind.

154
00:04:55.754 --> 00:04:56.796
You weren't so good with it.

155
00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:57.922
Just talk to Chelsea

156
00:04:57.922 --> 00:04:59.007
when you get to school tomorrow

157
00:04:59.007 --> 00:05:00.258
and make sure she knows

158
00:05:00.258 --> 00:05:01.551
you aren't gonna
rat her out to Billy.

159
00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:03.845
Yeah. Right. Okay.
That's a good plan.

160
00:05:03.845 --> 00:05:06.431
(groans) It's cold.
I think I can see my breath.

161
00:05:06.431 --> 00:05:07.766
I can taste Tina's.

162
00:05:07.766 --> 00:05:09.559
What? (exhales) Oh. yeah.

163
00:05:09.559 --> 00:05:11.603
Okay. let's go find Chelsea.

164
00:05:11.603 --> 00:05:13.104
- Hey. Tina.
- (Tina shouts)

165
00:05:13.104 --> 00:05:14.522
There's a note in my fanny pack

166
00:05:14.522 --> 00:05:15.982
that says you're a cheater.

167
00:05:15.982 --> 00:05:16.983
- What?
- And soon.

168
00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:18.109
everyone's gonna know it.

169
00:05:18.109 --> 00:05:19.944
I'm not a cheater.
Chelsea's a cheater.

170
00:05:19.944 --> 00:05:21.154
Well. then you're just like her.

171
00:05:21.154 --> 00:05:22.655
- No.
- You're two cheats in a pod.

172
00:05:22.655 --> 00:05:24.199
- No.
- Two Cheater Cottontails.

173
00:05:24.199 --> 00:05:26.409
- No.
- A couple of Cheater Sarsgaards.

174
00:05:26.409 --> 00:05:28.995
No! (panting)

175
00:05:28.995 --> 00:05:31.373
I got to talk to Chelsea.

176
00:05:31.373 --> 00:05:34.000
All right. the Tina train
is heading out of the station

177
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:35.669
if anyone wants
to jump on board.

178
00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:37.379
Toot. toot.
Wow. it's cold in here.

179
00:05:37.379 --> 00:05:39.631
- Tina. look outside.
- No school.

180
00:05:39.631 --> 00:05:41.841
- It's a snow day. baby!
- What?

181
00:05:41.841 --> 00:05:43.510
- (wind gusting)
- (Tina shouts)

182
00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:45.387
Also. we think
the heater is broken

183
00:05:45.387 --> 00:05:46.846
because we don't have heat.

184
00:05:46.846 --> 00:05:48.765
I guess she fought hard
all through yesterday.

185
00:05:48.765 --> 00:05:50.016
but she didn't make it.

186
00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:51.810
I'm wearing layers.
It's a dress shirt.

187
00:05:51.810 --> 00:05:53.103
You're gonna want layers.

188
00:05:53.103 --> 00:05:55.105
And the heat is off
in the restaurant.

189
00:05:55.105 --> 00:05:58.775
which is bad because
customers expect to have heat.

190
00:05:58.775 --> 00:05:59.943
I'm trying to
get through to Teddy.

191
00:05:59.943 --> 00:06:00.944
but he's not picking up.

192
00:06:00.944 --> 00:06:02.862
So. no work and no school.

193
00:06:02.862 --> 00:06:04.989
Wait. no.
I have to go to school!

194
00:06:04.989 --> 00:06:06.825
Aw. so excited to learn.

195
00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:09.327
<i>♪ If you need a lot of fish
in a jiffy ♪</i>

196
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:10.537
<i>♪ Call Jeffrey Ruth
Seafood Delivery ♪</i>

197
00:06:10.537 --> 00:06:12.330
- (Tina groans)
- (Linda sings gibberish)

198
00:06:17.043 --> 00:06:18.503
- (Tina groans)
- LOUISE: Look alive. Tina.

199
00:06:18.503 --> 00:06:19.504
We need your help.

200
00:06:19.504 --> 00:06:20.714
We need you to help bring

201
00:06:20.714 --> 00:06:22.507
every single pillow
and blanket you can find.

202
00:06:22.507 --> 00:06:23.925
We're building a pillow
and blanket fort

203
00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:26.386
'cause playing in the snow
didn't really work out.

204
00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:27.721
- Don't like it!
Don't like it! Don't...
- (Gene screaming)

205
00:06:27.721 --> 00:06:28.972
So. if we're gonna
enjoy this day.

206
00:06:28.972 --> 00:06:31.016
we have to stay warm.
and the first step

207
00:06:31.016 --> 00:06:32.767
to winter survival
is making a shelter.

208
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:35.061
I learned that from that show.
<i>Making A Shelter.</i>

209
00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:36.896
I can't help.
I'm busy doing this.

210
00:06:36.896 --> 00:06:37.897
(groaning)

211
00:06:37.897 --> 00:06:40.191
Tina. it's gonna
be a really long day

212
00:06:40.191 --> 00:06:41.776
if you spend it wishing
you were talking to

213
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.778
you-know-who
about you-know-what.

214
00:06:43.778 --> 00:06:45.530
She's talking about
how that girl Chelsea

215
00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:46.948
thinks you're a cheater.

216
00:06:46.948 --> 00:06:47.991
- (groaning)
- Come on.

217
00:06:47.991 --> 00:06:49.451
You can sulk inside our fort.

218
00:06:49.451 --> 00:06:50.618
That you're gonna help finish.

219
00:06:50.618 --> 00:06:52.495
But also please don't sulk
inside our fort.

220
00:06:52.495 --> 00:06:55.915
We're trying to curate kind of
a non-sulky vibe/experience.

221
00:06:55.915 --> 00:06:57.167
(groans) Fine.

222
00:06:57.167 --> 00:06:58.209
<i>LOUISE:
There's our girl.</i>

223
00:06:58.209 --> 00:06:59.919
<i>Now pillows and blankets. Mush!</i>

224
00:06:59.919 --> 00:07:01.880
<i>GENE:
And try to find
a nice accent piece.</i>

225
00:07:01.880 --> 00:07:03.965
Thanks for calling back. Teddy.

226
00:07:03.965 --> 00:07:06.343
Yeah. it's broken-broken.
Do you think you could come?

227
00:07:06.343 --> 00:07:09.054
Bob. I've literally
had this exact dream.

228
00:07:09.054 --> 00:07:10.305
Your heater breaks. I rush over.

229
00:07:10.305 --> 00:07:11.931
Linda is scared and so are you.

230
00:07:11.931 --> 00:07:13.933
but I look you both in the eyes
and I say.

231
00:07:13.933 --> 00:07:17.312
"Shh-shh. I'm here.
Teddy's here. You're fine."

232
00:07:17.312 --> 00:07:19.439
And we all hold hands
while I fix your heater.

233
00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:21.066
I don't know how
I do it with no hands.

234
00:07:21.066 --> 00:07:22.359
Maybe I use my feet?

235
00:07:22.359 --> 00:07:24.944
- Mm-hmm. So. can you come over?
<i>- I can't.</i>

236
00:07:24.944 --> 00:07:27.822
I'm headed to a job.
Ah. why do I take jobs?

237
00:07:27.822 --> 00:07:29.282
<i>- Oh. my God.</i>
- But don't worry.

238
00:07:29.282 --> 00:07:31.242
I know an
HVAC guy who's really good.

239
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:33.787
but you know. he's a sweet man.
Maybe a little sensitive.

240
00:07:33.787 --> 00:07:35.121
But. what does that mean?

241
00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:36.122
<i>Just don't razz him.</i>

242
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.540
I know you like to razz. Bob.

243
00:07:37.540 --> 00:07:39.501
<i>- I-I don't razz.</i>
- You roast. You razz.

244
00:07:39.501 --> 00:07:41.670
- Teddy. that's not true.
<i>- Ask anybody.</i>

245
00:07:41.670 --> 00:07:43.380
Teddy. I just want
our heater to work.

246
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:44.631
I'll send you his number.

247
00:07:44.631 --> 00:07:46.758
Boy. I hit the brakes.
like. 20 seconds ago

248
00:07:46.758 --> 00:07:49.344
and I'm still skidding.
I just slid right by my exit.

249
00:07:49.344 --> 00:07:50.512
Teddy. be careful.

250
00:07:50.512 --> 00:07:51.888
<i>Ah. you know what I'm gonna do?</i>

251
00:07:51.888 --> 00:07:53.682
<i>I'm gonna gently steer
into the guard rail.</i>

252
00:07:53.682 --> 00:07:55.558
- Teddy. don't do that.
<i>- Hell of a time for
a roast. Bobby.</i>

253
00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:57.352
- That wasn't a roast.
<i>- I'm just about to go into</i>

254
00:07:57.352 --> 00:07:59.187
<i>a guard rail.
and you're razzing me.</i>

255
00:07:59.187 --> 00:08:01.606
<i>Oh. I regained control.
but I should probably go.</i>

256
00:08:01.606 --> 00:08:02.982
LOUISE:
It's nice in here.

257
00:08:02.982 --> 00:08:04.401
Maybe nicer than our house?

258
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:06.361
Oh. my God. It's so cozy.

259
00:08:06.361 --> 00:08:08.863
There's my comforter.
Just right there on the floor.

260
00:08:08.863 --> 00:08:10.407
And I'm using your pillow
as my foot rest.

261
00:08:10.407 --> 00:08:12.117
My feet are gonna
smell like your face.

262
00:08:12.117 --> 00:08:13.952
No. Give it to me.
(sniffs. groans)

263
00:08:13.952 --> 00:08:15.203
It's too late. Keep it.

264
00:08:15.203 --> 00:08:16.496
Tina. you okay. sweetie?

265
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.081
You look anxious.
You have to poop?

266
00:08:18.081 --> 00:08:20.792
I'm great. So happy
we're not going to school.

267
00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:22.085
Well. it's gonna be
a little longer

268
00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:23.461
until the heat gets fixed today.

269
00:08:23.461 --> 00:08:24.754
Do you guys need anything?

270
00:08:24.754 --> 00:08:26.756
Hot cocoa please?
And just keep it coming?

271
00:08:26.756 --> 00:08:28.675
Yeah. okay.
You kids just stay here

272
00:08:28.675 --> 00:08:30.385
- and make everything smell bad.
- On it.

273
00:08:30.385 --> 00:08:32.804
Ugh. Teddy's heater guy
still isn't answering.

274
00:08:32.804 --> 00:08:34.014
Probably busy today.

275
00:08:34.014 --> 00:08:35.432
Or maybe he's out
making a snowman?

276
00:08:35.432 --> 00:08:36.850
It's just.
if you run a business.

277
00:08:36.850 --> 00:08:38.435
you should pick up
your ph... Hi.

278
00:08:38.435 --> 00:08:39.978
Hey. This is. uh. Bob Belcher.

279
00:08:39.978 --> 00:08:42.022
I got your number from Teddy.

280
00:08:42.022 --> 00:08:44.107
What-what did... What did I say?

281
00:08:44.107 --> 00:08:46.568
Oh. I said
if-if you run a business.

282
00:08:46.568 --> 00:08:47.902
you should pick up your phone.

283
00:08:47.902 --> 00:08:49.696
But I was talking
about something else.

284
00:08:49.696 --> 00:08:51.823
'cause you did
pick up your phone. Eventually.

285
00:08:51.823 --> 00:08:53.241
Hello? Oh. good.

286
00:08:53.241 --> 00:08:54.909
I-I thought you...
I thought you hung up.

287
00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:57.287
You're doing great. Bob.
But do it better.

288
00:08:57.287 --> 00:09:00.457
What a day.
No school. no restaurant.

289
00:09:00.457 --> 00:09:02.167
Bottomless hot cocoa on the way.

290
00:09:02.167 --> 00:09:04.210
Bottomless hot cocoa?
Yes. please.

291
00:09:04.210 --> 00:09:06.046
No. no-no-no.
You'll catch your death.

292
00:09:06.046 --> 00:09:07.672
- Keep your cheeks warm.
- Fine.

293
00:09:07.672 --> 00:09:10.175
<i>♪ Call Jeffrey Ruth
Seafood Delivery ♪</i>

294
00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:12.260
Nope. Nope. Nuh-uh. Not in here.

295
00:09:12.260 --> 00:09:13.511
Wait. where did Tina go?

296
00:09:13.511 --> 00:09:15.013
TINA (muffled):
I didn't cheat!

297
00:09:15.013 --> 00:09:17.307
There she is.
Tina. we have to fix you.

298
00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:18.808
For the sake
of the Pillow Palace.

299
00:09:18.808 --> 00:09:20.185
which is a name
I'm workshopping.

300
00:09:20.185 --> 00:09:22.145
- Cushion Castle?
- Damn it. that's better.

301
00:09:22.145 --> 00:09:23.396
The only thing that could fix me

302
00:09:23.396 --> 00:09:25.106
would be going to school
and talking to Chelsea.

303
00:09:25.106 --> 00:09:27.567
I'm gonna put the blanket back
over you. Night-night.

304
00:09:27.567 --> 00:09:29.444
Tina. there's some
exciting new technology

305
00:09:29.444 --> 00:09:31.321
I think you should know about.
It's called the telephone.

306
00:09:31.321 --> 00:09:32.614
Call Chelsea?

307
00:09:32.614 --> 00:09:34.199
I don't know the number
of whatever burner phone

308
00:09:34.199 --> 00:09:35.533
she's probably using right now.

309
00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:37.327
Mom and Dad have to
have a school directory

310
00:09:37.327 --> 00:09:38.453
around here somewhere. right?

311
00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:39.829
Oh. my God. School directory.

312
00:09:39.829 --> 00:09:41.414
Yeah. go ask Mom and Dad for it

313
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:43.041
and find out what's
going on with that cocoa.

314
00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:45.210
Yeah. this miss
needs some Swiss.

315
00:09:45.210 --> 00:09:46.670
He's gonna come. right?

316
00:09:46.670 --> 00:09:48.672
I feel like
we won't survive the night.

317
00:09:48.672 --> 00:09:50.215
And that's bad parenting.

318
00:09:50.215 --> 00:09:51.758
I mean he said
he was gonna come.

319
00:09:51.758 --> 00:09:52.926
Maybe-maybe I should
call him again.

320
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.761
Bob. it's fine. Get me the milk.

321
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:56.137
But wait. smell it first.

322
00:09:56.137 --> 00:09:58.306
(sniffs)
Let's say it's good enough.

323
00:09:58.306 --> 00:10:00.100
Hey. hey. hey.
Uh. I want to. um.

324
00:10:00.100 --> 00:10:01.601
call a friend from school

325
00:10:01.601 --> 00:10:03.269
that's always been my friend.

326
00:10:03.269 --> 00:10:05.146
So do you happen to have
the school directory handy?

327
00:10:05.146 --> 00:10:06.398
I forgot some of the numbers.

328
00:10:06.398 --> 00:10:08.525
I know there's a six.
just need a couple more.

329
00:10:08.525 --> 00:10:10.777
School directory.
Where have I seen that?

330
00:10:10.777 --> 00:10:12.821
Oh. I think it's under
the leg of our bed frame

331
00:10:12.821 --> 00:10:14.656
'cause the legs are uneven.

332
00:10:14.656 --> 00:10:16.449
Or our house is.
I'm not sure which.

333
00:10:16.449 --> 00:10:17.951
Uh. we didn't think
you kids would need it

334
00:10:17.951 --> 00:10:20.787
'cause you don't seem to
ever call anyone or do things.

335
00:10:20.787 --> 00:10:23.164
Not in a bad way.
You-you have each other.

336
00:10:23.164 --> 00:10:25.667
Um. I'm gonna go get it
from under your bed. Bye.

337
00:10:25.667 --> 00:10:28.128
Oh. and. uh. the Cushion Castle
is still waiting on that cocoa.

338
00:10:28.128 --> 00:10:29.212
Taste this.

339
00:10:29.212 --> 00:10:30.588
Oh. I was wrong. Milk's bad.

340
00:10:30.588 --> 00:10:31.923
Do you think they'll notice?

341
00:10:31.923 --> 00:10:33.758
I think start over.
Just use water.

342
00:10:33.758 --> 00:10:36.302
We shouldn't make our
kids drink old milk. right?

343
00:10:36.302 --> 00:10:38.138
Okay. Dr. Fresh Milk.

344
00:10:38.138 --> 00:10:41.224
I got it.
And apparently I can lift beds

345
00:10:41.224 --> 00:10:43.518
when I'm really stressed out.
Anyway. I'm calling her.

346
00:10:43.518 --> 00:10:45.020
Quick question.
Who would you guys call

347
00:10:45.020 --> 00:10:46.896
if you needed a lot of fish.
but in a jiffy?

348
00:10:46.896 --> 00:10:48.189
- Gene. no.
- It's ringing.

349
00:10:48.189 --> 00:10:50.483
Uh. hey. is this Chelsea?

350
00:10:50.483 --> 00:10:52.193
Hi. it's Tina. From school?

351
00:10:52.193 --> 00:10:53.278
Why are you calling me?

352
00:10:53.278 --> 00:10:55.030
Well. I was trying
to talk to you

353
00:10:55.030 --> 00:10:56.823
after the history test yesterday.

354
00:10:56.823 --> 00:10:58.408
but you kind of ran off there.

355
00:10:58.408 --> 00:11:02.078
Anyway. I just wanted to
talk about the. um. thing?

356
00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:03.788
Oh. you mean when you cheated?

357
00:11:03.788 --> 00:11:05.457
No. no. no. when you cheated.

358
00:11:05.457 --> 00:11:07.751
Sorry. Sorry. (nervous laughter)

359
00:11:07.751 --> 00:11:10.962
So. what? Are you calling just
to tell me you told on me?

360
00:11:10.962 --> 00:11:13.506
No. No. No. no. no. no. no.
I definitely didn't tell on you.

361
00:11:13.506 --> 00:11:16.051
And also. I wasn't cheating.
I-I got the right answer

362
00:11:16.051 --> 00:11:17.385
before I looked
at Susmita's test.

363
00:11:17.385 --> 00:11:18.636
So. I'm not a cheater.

364
00:11:18.636 --> 00:11:20.764
- Okay. great. Neither am I.
- Yup. great.

365
00:11:20.764 --> 00:11:23.266
So. uh. just. since
we're talking about it.

366
00:11:23.266 --> 00:11:26.227
um. did you tell on me?

367
00:11:26.227 --> 00:11:28.271
Oh. you know what? I might have.

368
00:11:28.271 --> 00:11:30.357
I might've written it
on like a little note

369
00:11:30.357 --> 00:11:33.151
and put it in that creepy
puppet's pocket or something.

370
00:11:33.151 --> 00:11:34.986
Fanny pack!
You put it in his fanny pack.

371
00:11:34.986 --> 00:11:37.113
Well. this has been fun. Bye.

372
00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:38.990
(gasping) She told on me.

373
00:11:38.990 --> 00:11:40.867
Chelsea told on me! (shouts)

374
00:11:40.867 --> 00:11:43.119
I don't know if the castle can
handle this kind of meltdown.

375
00:11:43.119 --> 00:11:44.996
- (Tina shouts)
- No. no. no. no. no.

376
00:11:44.996 --> 00:11:46.206
(shouting)

377
00:11:46.206 --> 00:11:47.457
GENE:
Hmm. kind of feels like

378
00:11:47.457 --> 00:11:48.833
we're just sitting on
the floor now. Gross.

379
00:11:53.505 --> 00:11:54.923
Ah! Chelsea told on me.

380
00:11:54.923 --> 00:11:56.549
But I didn't do anything.
I didn't cheat off Susmita.

381
00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:58.843
Oh. no. What's sweet. sweet
Susmita going to think of me?

382
00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:01.096
I'll just switch schools.
Or Susmita should.

383
00:12:01.096 --> 00:12:02.972
Or we both should?
How does this work?

384
00:12:02.972 --> 00:12:04.933
I can't believe my life is being
ruined by a stupid puppet.

385
00:12:04.933 --> 00:12:06.893
Oh wait. Mr. Frond's puppet.

386
00:12:06.893 --> 00:12:09.562
You know what. I'm just gonna
text the heater guy real quick.

387
00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.940
Maybe I'll just casually
send him our address.

388
00:12:11.940 --> 00:12:14.025
- So he has it.
- You already told him
where we were.

389
00:12:14.025 --> 00:12:15.443
Well. now
he'll have it in writing.

390
00:12:15.443 --> 00:12:18.697
"Here is our address again."
(groans) New phone.

391
00:12:18.697 --> 00:12:21.658
Not good at texting on it.
And... send.

392
00:12:21.658 --> 00:12:22.992
- Oh. my God.
- What?

393
00:12:22.992 --> 00:12:24.994
It wrote "again"
in all caps somehow.

394
00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:26.371
So. now it's like
I'm yelling at him.

395
00:12:26.371 --> 00:12:28.206
Like. "Here is
our address AGAIN."

396
00:12:28.206 --> 00:12:29.791
I told you not to text him.

397
00:12:29.791 --> 00:12:32.168
I'm going to apologize.
"My bad."

398
00:12:32.168 --> 00:12:34.421
- Wait. no. Oh. my God.
- What?

399
00:12:34.421 --> 00:12:36.297
It autocorrected
"bad" to "butt."

400
00:12:36.297 --> 00:12:38.174
so I just texted him. "My butt."

401
00:12:38.174 --> 00:12:40.385
Just stop. Bob.
Put down the phone.

402
00:12:40.385 --> 00:12:43.346
Okay. I just wrote. "My bad.
Not my butt. Please still come."

403
00:12:43.346 --> 00:12:44.389
Okay. good save.

404
00:12:44.389 --> 00:12:45.390
I'm bringing the super special.

405
00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:46.891
no-spoiled-milk cocoa

406
00:12:46.891 --> 00:12:48.643
to our maybe
slightly spoiled kids.

407
00:12:48.643 --> 00:12:50.228
Don't call anyone.
don't text anyone.

408
00:12:50.228 --> 00:12:51.354
Uh. I'm calling Teddy.

409
00:12:51.354 --> 00:12:52.814
LINDA:
Just stop calling people!

410
00:12:52.814 --> 00:12:53.857
It's going to voice mail.

411
00:12:53.857 --> 00:12:56.443
Teddy. it's Bob.
Um. I think I did bad.

412
00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:57.694
I might need you
to call that guy

413
00:12:57.694 --> 00:12:58.945
and tell him that I'm nice.

414
00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:01.531
and that-that
we don't deserve to die.

415
00:13:01.531 --> 00:13:03.742
Really good cocoa time.

416
00:13:03.742 --> 00:13:05.410
Just a second. Mom.
We weren't expecting

417
00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:07.537
a teen-nado to destroy
our precious palace.

418
00:13:07.537 --> 00:13:10.331
But I think we've built back
better. stronger. cozier.

419
00:13:10.331 --> 00:13:12.292
What happened? Where's Tina?
What's going on?

420
00:13:12.292 --> 00:13:13.501
She's fine. she's fine.

421
00:13:13.501 --> 00:13:15.128
Nothing you need
to concern yourself with.

422
00:13:15.128 --> 00:13:16.838
Some might blame
the lateness of the cocoa.

423
00:13:16.838 --> 00:13:18.340
but I think that's unfair.

424
00:13:18.340 --> 00:13:20.300
I'm here. Hi. Thank you. Mom.
I'll take those.

425
00:13:20.300 --> 00:13:21.843
And off you go.
Back to the kitchen.

426
00:13:21.843 --> 00:13:23.053
Heh. Oh. not to be sexist.

427
00:13:23.053 --> 00:13:24.512
I might go to a different room.

428
00:13:24.512 --> 00:13:26.556
Nah. I'm going to the kitchen.

429
00:13:26.556 --> 00:13:27.557
I'm gonna heat up some crackers.

430
00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:29.142
Hey. So. we're glad you're back.

431
00:13:29.142 --> 00:13:31.269
and we're hoping you're
not gonna go all standy-uppy.

432
00:13:31.269 --> 00:13:33.563
The insurance company
paid for the repairs.

433
00:13:33.563 --> 00:13:35.148
but we don't want to
go through that again.

434
00:13:35.148 --> 00:13:37.108
We're still
rebuilding emotionally.

435
00:13:37.108 --> 00:13:39.569
I have an idea. I just need
the school directory again.

436
00:13:39.569 --> 00:13:40.695
There's someone
I have to talk to.

437
00:13:40.695 --> 00:13:42.447
- Who are you calling?
- Mr. Frond.

438
00:13:42.447 --> 00:13:43.990
I can get ahead of this.
I just have to tell him

439
00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:45.784
that there's a note in Billy's
fanny pack that's not true.

440
00:13:45.784 --> 00:13:48.203
Sounds like a desperate. last
ditch effort to save yourself.

441
00:13:48.203 --> 00:13:49.621
- Thank you. It's ringing.
- (line ringing)

442
00:13:49.621 --> 00:13:51.664
(TV music playing)

443
00:13:51.664 --> 00:13:53.750
No. Phillip.
Don't answer the phone.

444
00:13:53.750 --> 00:13:56.753
Not until the glutes and quads
cooldown routine.

445
00:13:56.753 --> 00:13:59.381
You owe it to them because
they are on fire right now.

446
00:13:59.381 --> 00:14:01.549
No answer. Crap.
Crap. crap. crap.

447
00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:04.386
Sorry. T. Guess you'll just have
to deal with Billy tomorrow.

448
00:14:04.386 --> 00:14:05.637
No. I'm calling back.

449
00:14:05.637 --> 00:14:07.389
- (phone ringing)
- Leave me alone.

450
00:14:07.389 --> 00:14:09.391
I'm toning. (groans)

451
00:14:09.391 --> 00:14:10.975
Dang it. Okay. okay.

452
00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:12.352
You know what's better
than a phone call?

453
00:14:12.352 --> 00:14:14.312
Me going to Mr. Frond's house.
He has to be home.

454
00:14:14.312 --> 00:14:16.189
And I know where he lives.
And-and if he's not home.

455
00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:17.565
I'll wait for him.
Or I'll find him.

456
00:14:17.565 --> 00:14:19.526
I'll hunt him down.
I'll get his scent. track him.

457
00:14:19.526 --> 00:14:21.528
and then I tell him.
"You gonna believe me

458
00:14:21.528 --> 00:14:22.779
or you gonna
believe that puppet?"

459
00:14:22.779 --> 00:14:24.072
And he's gonna look in my eyes.

460
00:14:24.072 --> 00:14:25.990
and he's gonna believe me.
I love this plan.

461
00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:26.991
How are you gonna get there?

462
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:29.661
With these two bad girls.
My feet.

463
00:14:29.661 --> 00:14:31.413
They taste just like
regular crackers.

464
00:14:31.413 --> 00:14:32.956
but they're hot.
And I love them.

465
00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:34.332
They feel good
on your face. too.

466
00:14:34.332 --> 00:14:35.667
<i>Bum-buh. ba-dippy ♪</i>

467
00:14:35.667 --> 00:14:37.377
Ooh. Mm. crackers. Mm. crackers.

468
00:14:37.377 --> 00:14:38.920
Lin. what are we gonna do
if he doesn't come?

469
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:40.505
I don't think
we can stay here tonight.

470
00:14:40.505 --> 00:14:43.216
We could all pile into the kids'
little blanket castle thing.

471
00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:46.052
It'll be breathy.
but maybe kind of warmish?

472
00:14:46.052 --> 00:14:48.179
I don't know. I think we might
have to go to a hotel.

473
00:14:48.179 --> 00:14:50.306
Or probably a motel.
'cause poor.

474
00:14:50.306 --> 00:14:51.683
Wait. could we even get there?

475
00:14:51.683 --> 00:14:53.184
I don't think our car
can drive in this.

476
00:14:53.184 --> 00:14:54.728
Oh. my God.
we might be stuck here.

477
00:14:54.728 --> 00:14:56.229
Bob. you're freaking me out!

478
00:14:56.229 --> 00:14:57.981
Uh. give me... Give me
more crackers. More crackers.

479
00:14:57.981 --> 00:14:59.441
I'm putting them on my face.
Put them on your face.

480
00:14:59.441 --> 00:15:00.692
- Ow.
- What?

481
00:15:00.692 --> 00:15:02.777
I don't want
hot crackers on my face.

482
00:15:02.777 --> 00:15:04.237
- They're hot.
- You get used to it.

483
00:15:04.237 --> 00:15:06.072
