507
00:15:51.242 --> 00:15:53.078
Tell them I went
for a... stroll?

508
00:15:53.078 --> 00:15:54.412
Winter storm stroll. Got it.

509
00:15:54.412 --> 00:15:55.663
That sounds delightful.

510
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:57.582
Enjoy yourself
out there. sister.

511
00:15:57.582 --> 00:16:00.210
- (wind gusting)
- (shivering)

512
00:16:00.210 --> 00:16:01.461
Oh. my God. So cold.

513
00:16:01.461 --> 00:16:02.962
The truth
is not warm enough.

514
00:16:07.592 --> 00:16:10.053
(panting)
How long have I been out here?

515
00:16:10.053 --> 00:16:11.846
Oh. Hi. restaurant.

516
00:16:11.846 --> 00:16:13.264
Do you kids want hot crackers?

517
00:16:13.264 --> 00:16:14.933
Your mother and I
are having hot crackers.

518
00:16:14.933 --> 00:16:16.434
We don't know if the heater guy
is coming or not

519
00:16:16.434 --> 00:16:17.894
and it's nobody's fault.

520
00:16:17.894 --> 00:16:19.646
- It's my fault.
- It's your father's fault.

521
00:16:19.646 --> 00:16:21.523
Had a really bad phone call.

522
00:16:21.523 --> 00:16:23.441
A couple of them.
Some bad texts. too. Sorry.

523
00:16:23.441 --> 00:16:26.069
Ooh. yes to crackers.
Also. more cocoa please.

524
00:16:26.069 --> 00:16:28.697
- GENE: Me. too.
- Tina. you want one. too?

525
00:16:28.697 --> 00:16:29.781
GENE (imitating Tina):
Yes.

526
00:16:29.781 --> 00:16:31.199
Um. Gene.

527
00:16:31.199 --> 00:16:32.826
GENE:
No?

528
00:16:32.826 --> 00:16:34.285
Uh. did you murder Tina?

529
00:16:34.285 --> 00:16:35.370
W-Where's Tina?

530
00:16:35.370 --> 00:16:36.579
That's her. isn't it?

531
00:16:36.579 --> 00:16:38.373
That is not. That is a pillow.

532
00:16:38.373 --> 00:16:40.125
- What?
- Kids. where's your sister?

533
00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:41.751
She went for a stroll.

534
00:16:41.751 --> 00:16:43.878
A totally normal
winter storm stroll.

535
00:16:43.878 --> 00:16:45.130
- LINDA: What?
- She's outside?

536
00:16:45.130 --> 00:16:46.506
(wind gusting)

537
00:16:46.506 --> 00:16:47.841
<i>LINDA: I can't see her.
I can't see her.</i>

538
00:16:47.841 --> 00:16:50.135
Oh. my God. Bob.
she's gonna freeze to death.

539
00:16:50.135 --> 00:16:51.219
Like an Encino Man.

540
00:16:51.219 --> 00:16:52.971
I'll go find her. Louise?

541
00:16:52.971 --> 00:16:54.431
Got any tips which
direction I should go?

542
00:16:54.431 --> 00:16:56.099
- Towards Mr. Frond's house?
- What?

543
00:16:56.099 --> 00:16:57.600
I'm just using that
as a direction.

544
00:16:57.600 --> 00:16:59.686
like some people say.
"Go towards the water."

545
00:16:59.686 --> 00:17:01.354
You know. go towards
Mr. Frond's house.

546
00:17:01.354 --> 00:17:02.731
GENE:
Frond-ward.

547
00:17:02.731 --> 00:17:04.733
(shivering)

548
00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.276
Nice day for a walk. huh?

549
00:17:06.276 --> 00:17:08.111
Ah! Accountability Billy?

550
00:17:08.111 --> 00:17:09.821
Uh. it seems like you're
going around my back

551
00:17:09.821 --> 00:17:11.656
